20/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Council of Europe (CoE) Human Rights Commissioner Alvaro Gil-Robles launches a three-day visit to Tirana starting Sunday (20 October). 
He wants to gather information about the rights of women and children and protection from trafficking, and will meet with President Alfred Moisiu, members of the cabinet and NGOs dealing with human rights protection.
In other news, Spartak Ngjela, head of the Parliamentary Investigation Commission on State Information Service activity, demanded Saturday that politicians who had co-operated with the secret service leave their posts. 
He says the commission has evidence that secret service officials abused their power. 
(ATA, BTA - 19/10/02)
